post_text: This is important information for our families who have SNAP benefits or those whose student(s) were eligible for free and reduced-priced meals for the 19-20 school year. Please check this out! #byngpride
shared_text:
Oklahoma State Department of Education
July 8 at 1:02 PM ¬∑

Attn: Families!! We have partnered with Oklahoma Human Services to provide extra food benefits for families due to COVID-19. Under this new plan, current households receiving SNAP benefits *AND* non-SNAP households that include children eligible for free and reduced-priced meals, will automatically receive benefits without needing to complete an application.

Benefits will be issued for the 44-day period that schools were closed at the end of the 2019-20 school year and are equivalent to the daily reimbursement for free breakfast and lunch. Benefits will be automatically issued in staggered allotments by August 30. Families already receiving SNAP will receive the benefits on their cards.‚Ä¶

post_text:
We have exciting news!
For the 2020-21 school year Byng is offering all students either a traditional school option or a full-time virtual education program. We are committed to meeting the diverse needs of our students and are excited to offer these options to families.

For families who choose traditional school, we are working on protocol to ensure students can do so safely, and will be releasing more information about that soon.

Our virtual school students will be able to stay enrolled at Byng, learn from home, and continue to participate in extra-curricular activities. Anyone interested in enrolling their student(s) in virtual school should fill out the the form found here: https://forms.gle/Cunv6VXYjae6Ey9XA
#byngpride

June 25 at 11:44 PM ¬∑

2020-2021 BHS Cheer Tryout information

* Must be enrolled in the Byng School System .
*Highschool squad is made up of 9th -12th grade students.
*Must have a current physical on file with Byng Public Schools pryor to the tryout.(free athletic physical dates set up at Central Oklahoma Medical Center. 10th-12th grade 4-6pm and 7th-9th grade at 6- 8pm. (The physical papers can be found on the Byng School website)

Important Dates
*Tuesday- July 28th, 7pm in the HS gym, Meeting for all students interested in trying out! (PARTICIPANTS ONLY)

*Tuesday- August 4th, 5 to 7pm in the HS gym, learn tryout material and practice!

*Wednesday- August 5th, 5 to 7pm in the HS gym, practice for tryout!

*Thursday August 6th, 5 to 7pm in the HS gym, mock tryouts!

*Friday August 7th, 5 to 7pm in the HS gym, tryouts!

With any questions, please call Vanessa Lee @ (580) 320-9060 or by email vanessa.lee@byngschools.org

Please help us get the word out to our students!

On May 19th (10 a.m.-3 p.m.) and May 20th (10 a.m.-12 p.m.) stations will be set up in the Francis parking lot for families to drive through and pick up student supplies.

Here's what to expect at each station:

Station 1: Student Supplies, personal items, spring pictures, group pictures and report cards/progress reports will be available for pick-up.

Station 2: Please bring any school library books or text books to drop off in the designated tubs.

The free grab and go breakfast and lunch meals will continue to be offered. You can pick up (at Byng or Homer), or look for our bus deliveries 5 days a week! Email info@byngschools.org for information about when/where delivery is in your area.

We owe a huge thanks to Reneay Owens Smith and her staff, all our bus drivers, and those who ride the bus each day. It is because of their dedication and service that we can continue to offer this to our community!
#stayathome #mealdelivery #ByngPride

shared_text:

March 27 at 11:19 AM ¬∑

Dillon Atkinson, along with so many other amazing Byng employees, have been out here every morning driving buses to deliver food to our kiddos during the school closings. We love and miss our kids more than you can imagine. Getting to see the smile on their face when we deliver breakfast and lunch is priceless. Reneay Owens Smith and her staff have been so amazing throughout this process. They‚Äôve been working nonstop to prepare delicious meals for our kids! We fed 604 kids today! Keep spreading the word so more of our kids can have a meal!! I‚Äôm so thankful for the people I work with and the school I work for. #ByngPride

post_text:
Amazing STEM opportunity for two Byng students!
Are you a Byng 9th ‚Äì 11th grader who will be 13-17 years old on Jun 1, 2020? If so, then you are eligible to apply for our JASON Learning Argonaut Program! TWO Byng students will be chosen by JASON Learning officials to participate in a research expedition. Some of last years expeditions included studying about the Amazon Rainforest in Peru, learning about design thinking in San Fransisco, and researching sea turtles in the Bahamas! You have from now until December 13th, 2019 to apply.

You can go to https://www.jason.org/argonauts to learn more information or go here to begin your application https://jasonlearning.submittable.com/submit/146723/jason-student-argonaut-application-2020-phase-1?target=blank
shared_text:
JASON Learning | JASON‚Äôs Argonaut Program
JASON‚Äôs Student and Teacher Argonauts‚Äînamed after the band of explorers in Greek mythology who accompanied the hero Jason in his quest to find the Golden Fleece‚Äîtravel to locations around the world to work side-by-side with scientists and engineers.

text:
Amazing STEM opportunity for two Byng students!
Are you a Byng 9th ‚Äì 11th grader who will be 13-17 years old on Jun 1, 2020? If so, then you are eligible to apply for our JASON Learning Argonaut Program! TWO Byng students will be chosen by JASON Learning officials to participate in a research expedition. Some of last years expeditions included studying about the Amazon Rainforest in Peru, learning about design thinking in San Fransisco, and researching sea turtles in the Bahamas! You have from now until December 13th, 2019 to apply.

You can go to https://www.jason.org/argonauts to learn more information or go here to begin your application https://jasonlearning.submittable.com/submit/146723/jason-student-argonaut-application-2020-phase-1?target=blank

post_text: We are so excited about our new CyberPatriot Teams!! #ByngPride
shared_text:
Byng STEM
October 11, 2019 at 1:25 PM ¬∑

Did you know...
‚ûñAbout 25% of American families have been affected by cyber-crimes, like identity theft?
‚ûñThe US military considers cyber-attacks one of the greatest threats to national security and our economy?
‚ûñThere are over 300 thousand jobs currently open in the cyber-security field?

CyberPatriot is a cyber-security competition created by the Air Force Association to prepare students for life and careers in the digital world. The competition involves securing a virtual network that has a number of vulnerabilities.

Today, Byng High School‚Äôs first-ever CyberPatriot teams did a practice round in preparation for the actual competition. Byng registered three teams made up of students enrolled in Computer Science or Computer Repair. The official competition starts Friday, October 25.
